    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="930"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/2486: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-30">April 30,
                            1941</date>.<lb/>[Received April 30—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Senior Consul formally notified Shanghai Municipal Council this morning that
                    concerned powers have given their consent to the establishment <pb facs="0871"
                        n="861" xml:id="pg_861"/> of provisional council as set forth in resolution
                    no. 4 adopted at the ratepayers’ meeting on April 17. It is expected that the
                    new provisional council will assume office within next few days.</p>
                <p>Sent to Chungking. Repeated to Department and Peiping. Air mail to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
